item.title:
Towards a detection of reactor $\overline{
u}^{}_e 	o \overline{
u}^{}_\mu$ and $\overline{
u}^{}_e 	o \overline{
u}^{}_	au$ oscillations with possible CP violation

item.description:
arXiv:2509.00422v1 Announce Type: new Abstract: We propose an unprecedented detection of reactor $\overline{
u}^{}_e 	o \overline{
u}^{}_\mu$ and $\overline{
u}^{}_e 	o \overline{
u}^{}_	au$ oscillations by using elastic antineutrino-electron scattering processes $\overline{
u}^{}_\alpha + e^- 	o \overline{
u}^{}_\alpha + e^-$ (for $\alpha = e, \mu, 	au$), among which the $\overline{
u}^{}_e$ events can be singled out by accurately measuring the $\overline{
u}^{}_e$ flux via the inverse beta decay $\overline{
u}^{}_e + p 	o e^+ + n$. A proof-of-concept study shows that such measurements will not only be able to test the conservation of probability for reactor antineutrino oscillations, but also offer a new possibility to probe leptonic CP violation at the one-loop level.

arXiv:2509.02006v1 Announce Type: new Abstract: We study heavy-hadron semileptonic decays proceeding via $b 	o c$ transition, such as $B 	o D^{(*)}	au ar{
u}_	au$ and $\Lambda_b 	o \Lambda_c	au ar{
u}_	au$. In the heavy-quark limit, where the heavy-quark symmetry holds, we construct a general heavy-quark sum rule for these decays based on the spin decomposition picture. The relation holds directly for the squared amplitudes without requiring phase-space integration. We then apply this relation to reproduce the sum rule among $B 	o D^{(*)}	au ar{
u}_	au$ and $\Lambda_b 	o \Lambda_c	au ar{
u}_	au$. Furthermore, we extend the analysis to $\Omega_b 	o \Omega_c^{(*)}$ transitions and those involving excited states, such as $B 	o \{D_0^*,D_1^*\}$ and $B 	o \{D_1,D_2^*\}$.
